56.1	Health_care_reform_in_the_United_States	Health care reform in the United States	Health care reform in the United States has a long history. This article covers two federal statutes enacted in 2010: the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act (PPACA), signed March 23, 2010, and the Health Care and Education Reconciliation Act of 2010 , which amended the PPACA and became law on March 30.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/U.S._Uninsured_and_Uninsured_Rate_%281987_to_2008%29.JPG/400px-U.S._Uninsured_and_Uninsured_Rate_%281987_to_2008%29.JPG
